id: pm-08sv
title: "Extension-contributed project profiles: api.registerProfile end-to-end"
description: "Close the one remaining gap in the extension authoring tripod: the ExtensionApi exposes 14 register* surfaces (commands, flags, item types/fields, migrations, renderers, parser/preflight/service overrides, importers/exporters, search providers, vector store adapters) but NO way to contribute a PROJECT PROFILE. A profile is the single most powerful customization primitive — it bundles item types + custom statuses + fields + per-type workflows + config knobs + create templates + package recommendations into one declarative archetype that `pm profile apply` stages idempotently. Today `pm profile list/show/apply` resolves ONLY from the 3 core-baked BUILTIN_PROFILES (agile/ops/research). The SDK already ships defineProjectProfile (authoring identity) and packages/pm-kanban exports a kanbanProfile ProjectProfileDefinition, but it is UNREACHABLE: there is no `pm profile apply kanban` path because nothing registers it. This makes the 'any project archetype models its domain natively' promise of epic pm-8jdc incomplete for third-party packages."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[6]: "area:config","area:extensions","area:schema",living-map,pm-cli,sdk
created_at: "2026-06-29T09:01:56.236Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-29T13:39:51.899Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-ugqx
resolution: "Completed the extension-contributed profile feature across core registerProfile, profile resolution, SDK parity, docs/contracts, and pm-kanban dogfood."
expected_result: The pm SDK and CLI expose project profiles as a universal customization primitive so packages can model domain archetypes and agents can apply them with pm profile list/show/apply.
actual_result: "PR #401 ships registerProfile end to end; the closeout branch verifies focused tests, isolated installed-package smoke, full 100/100/100/100 coverage, static/contract/security gates, package doctor, health, and Sentry/telemetry."
