close_reason: "Extension-contributed project profiles are shipped, documented, dogfooded, and verified end to end."
body: "## Gap\n\n`ExtensionApi` has 14 `register*` methods; profiles are the only authoring surface in the SDK barrel (`defineProjectProfile`) with no `register*` counterpart. `pm profile list/show/apply` reads only `BUILTIN_PROFILES` (agile/ops/research). `packages/pm-kanban` exports `kanbanProfile` but it can never reach `pm profile`.\n\n## Design\n\n- **Capability**: reuse the existing `schema` capability (a profile is fundamentally a schema+config bundle; an extension registering a profile already needs `schema` to apply its types/fields). No capability-contract version bump.\n- **Policy surface**: add `schema.profiles` to `KNOWN_EXTENSION_POLICY_SURFACES`, alongside `schema.itemtypes`/`schema.migrations`.\n- **Registry**: new `RegisteredExtensionProjectProfile { layer, name, profile }`; `ExtensionRegistrationRegistry.profiles`; `ExtensionRegistrationCounts.profiles`.\n- **Loader**: `api.registerProfile(profile)` validates the definition, gates on `schema` + `schema.profiles`, pushes to `registrations.profiles`.\n- **Resolution**: `pm profile list/show/apply` merges `getActiveExtensionRegistrations()?.profiles` with `BUILTIN_PROFILES`; builtin names are reserved (extension collision warns + is ignored); each profile carries a `source` (builtin | package name) surfaced in CLI/MCP output.\n- **SDK**: `assertRegisteredProfile` testing helper (declarative surface → assert only, mirroring item types/fields); `composeExtension` blueprint `profiles` auto-wires `registerProfile`; `deriveExtensionCapabilities` maps profiles → `schema`; `describeExtensionActivation`/`describeExtensionBlueprint`/markdown include profiles.\n- **Dogfood**: `packages/pm-kanban` calls `api.registerProfile(kanbanProfile)` so `pm profile apply kanban` works once installed — the live exemplar.\n- **Docs**: SDK.md / EXTENSIONS.md document the surface.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- `pm profile list` shows extension-registered profiles with their source.\n- `pm profile apply <extension-profile>` stages it idempotently like a builtin.\n- Full `define→register→assert→describe→derive→compose` parity for profiles.\n- 100% test + docstring coverage; full.json + contracts regenerated; bots green."
